      <exercise id="fs-id1169737713077" type="problems-exercises">
        <problem id="fs-id1169737847166">
          <para id="import-auto-id1169737763964">What angle would the axis of a polarizing filter need to make with the direction of polarized light of intensity <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>00</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:msup><m:mtext>kW/m</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{1 "." "00"`"kW/m" rSup { size 8{2} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> to reduce the intensity to <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>10</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:msup><m:mtext>W/m</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{10 "." 0`"W/m" rSup { size 8{2} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>?</para></problem></exercise>

